
[1]griping

   GRIPING, ppr. Grasping; seizing; holding fast; pinching; oppressing;
   distressing the bowels.

   GRIPING,n. A pinching or grasp; a distressing pain of the bowels;
   colic.

   1. In seamen's language, the inclination of a ship to run to the
   windward of her course.
